ygData.messageBody:
Sorry to hear that. I can sympathyse with you as I
work long hours as well.I work twelve hours shifts and
on the days I work I cannot EQ due to the fact that I
only have a few hours to sleep that day. I usually
work twelve hours then wait to be releived and then
drive home then sleep for a couple of hours till
someone calls (someone always does),usually someone
who is sure I should be awake but am not. So my sleep
pattern is off.But that is making a long story of it,I
just wanted to let you know someone else understands.
Take care,things will get better. Woodelfdee of EQ
